  "title": "Unable to modify configure settings using setIndexUIState ",
  "body": "### 🐛 Current behavior\n\nSeems it is not possible to change `configure` settings via `setIndexUiState`. When attempting to do so, the `configure` key gets removed from the state tree..`\r\n\r\nI'm using a state mapping that keeps the `configure` key in the state after finding that the `simple` mapping was removing it (https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/5892)\n\n### 🔍 Steps to reproduce\n\nOpen the code sandbox and click the `Change Distinct settings` button.\n\n### Live reproduction\n\nhttps://codesandbox.io/s/inspiring-water-c5mcv4?file=/src/App.tsx\n\n### 💭 Expected behavior\n\nI think it should let you change the distinct (and other settings as well) using `setIndexUiState.`\n\n### Package version\n\n7.2.0\n\n### Operating system\n\n_No response_\n\n### Browser\n\n_No response_\n\n### Code of Conduct\n\n- [X] I agree to follow this project's Code of Conduct",
